{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":36310,"record_hash":"sha256:e4d3225c8d4a7cf0bf9ba4e9708b886970d95bd328a2ceefaa5aa558937da961","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:52:38.554Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/session-association-strategy.md\n@@\n The safest design line is:\n \n ```text\n-inference may suggest; only explicit or high-confidence confirmation should persist\n+inference may suggest or preselect; confirmed user/API intent persists\n ```\n@@\n | Evidence/recompute | Store or derive evidence from time, files, tool calls, and patch similarity; compute links later. | Can power useful suggestions without mutating metadata. | Privacy, performance, explainability, and false-positive risk. | Use for suggestions only, not durable truth. |\n | Active session pin | User marks a session as \"for this work\"; later commit/PR UI preselects it. | Reduces detective work. Helps handoff before code exists. | Can go stale. Needs obvious clear/expiry behavior. | Possible UX shortcut. |\n+\n+## Useful Shortcuts\n+\n+- **PR/review prep picker:** at the moment the user is about to share work, show\n+  recent sessions with previews and let them attach the relevant ones. This\n+  avoids lifecycle propagation while directly serving the review use case.\n+- **Suggest, do not write:** rank sessions from time, files, tool names, and\n+  visible transcript text, but keep those rankings as UI help until confirmed.\n+- **Active session pin:** let the user mark the current session as related to\n+  the work in progress. Commit or PR UI can then preselect it without guessing.\n+- **Derived branch/PR views:** store links on durable lower-level targets when\n+  they exist, then let branch and PR views union those links.\n+- **Selected session snapshot:** if a